\begin_inset Formula $p_{\theta}-c-\tau V(\theta)$
\end_inset

 if he accepts it, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau V(\theta)$
\end_inset

 is the opportunity cost of lost value for working on the task for time
 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

.
 seller optimization problem is then the system of the following two equations:
\begin_inset Note Comment
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
I still use this formulation because in the alternative I have to differentiate
 
\begin_inset Formula $F(c)$
\end_inset

 which is not differentiable in the general case.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
V(\theta) & = & \beta_{A}\int\pi(c,\theta)dF_{\theta}^{\mu}(c)\label{eq:V-via-pi-1}\\
\pi(c,\theta) & = & \max\{0,p_{\theta}-c-\tau V(\theta)\}\label{eq:pi(c)-1}
\end{eqnarray}

