For each 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

, seller strategy is function 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma(\cdot,\theta)\colon c\to[0,1]$
\end_inset

 that maps the expected cost of a task to the probability of accepting it.
 For each 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 the seller acceptance rate is the ex ante probability of accepting a task:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\alpha(\theta)=\int\sigma(c,\theta)dF_{\theta}^{\mu}(c).\label{eq:alpha-1}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


