\begin_layout Standard
The next lemma shows how to find arrival rate for available sellers 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{A}$
\end_inset

 as a function of acceptance rates.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Lemma
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "lem:D_A"

\end_inset

For an arbitrary vector of acceptance rates 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha(\theta)$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha(\theta)\in[0,1]$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{A}$
\end_inset

 is the unique solution to 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\int\frac{G(d\theta)}{\tau\alpha(\theta)+1/\beta_{A}}=\beta.\label{eq:beta_A}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the proof I show that the steady state utilization rate is 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho(\theta)=1-\frac{1}{\tau\alpha(\theta)\beta_{A}+1}$
\end_inset

, which yields 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
