The uniqueness obtains by monotonicity of reaction curves in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "eq:alpha"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "eq:beta_A"

\end_inset

.
 Namely, in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "eq:alpha"

\end_inset

, as buyer traffic intensity 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{A}$
\end_inset

 increases, sellers become more picky and acceptance rate 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha(\theta)$
\end_inset

 decreases.
 In 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "eq:beta_A"

\end_inset

, as 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha(\theta)$
\end_inset

 increases, buyers get directed to a smaller set of sellers, hence 
