\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "prop:Equilibrium-exists-and"

\end_inset

 demonstrates the role of capacity utilization in two-sided markets.
 Both buyers and sellers are price-takers.
 The result shows that for any price 
\begin_inset Formula $p>0$
\end_inset

 and any segmentation 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

, there is a steady-state equilibrium characterized by the vector of acceptance
 rates 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\alpha(\theta)\right)$
\end_inset

 where the market clears.
 This happens because there are two mechanisms to clear the market: through
 adjustments in price and through adjustments in capacity utilization.
 The former is the most familiar mechanism, but in this paper I emphasize
 the importance of the latter.
 
\end_layout

